# Always Use Heroicons for Icons

In the client app, use **@heroicons/vue** for all UI icons. Do not add inline `<svg>` markup for icons.

## Usage

- **Import** from `@heroicons/vue/24/outline` or `@heroicons/vue/24/solid`:
  ```js
  import { IconNameIcon } from '@heroicons/vue/24/outline';
  ```
- **Use the component** in the template with size/color classes:
  ```vue
  <IconNameIcon class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500" />
  ```
- Prefer **outline** icons for most UI; use **solid** when you need emphasis (e.g. primary actions, selected state).

## When Adding or Replacing Icons

1. Find the matching Heroicon at [heroicons.com](https://heroicons.com) (same concept: calendar, user, list, close, etc.).
2. Import it from `@heroicons/vue/24/outline` (or `/24/solid`).
3. Replace any existing inline `<svg>…</svg>` with the component.

## Common Mappings

| Purpose        | Outline icon           | Solid (if needed)   |
|----------------|------------------------|---------------------|
| Close / cancel | XMarkIcon              | —                   |
| Calendar       | CalendarIcon, CalendarDaysIcon | —         |
| User / person  | UserIcon               | —                   |
| List           | ListBulletIcon         | —                   |
| Columns/kanban | ViewColumnsIcon       | —                   |
| Search         | MagnifyingGlassIcon    | —                   |
| Empty/inbox    | InboxIcon, ArchiveBoxIcon | —                |

Existing inline SVGs in the codebase should be gradually replaced with Heroicons when touching those files.
